<TITLE> PM seeks more US investment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 29 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Monday called for increased US investments in Bangladesh's infrastructure, power and energy sectors. Hasina made the appeal when the visiting US congress members David Price, Jeff Fortenderry and Stephen Lynch called on her at her Sher-e-Bangla Nagar residence, deputy press secretary Mahbubul Haque Shakil said. The prime minister also pointed out that the country was without a democratic government for a long time and that her government is currently working to strengthen the democratic institutions and ensuring good governance through the parliament. She also expressed hopes that the good relations between US and Bangladesh will be further strengthened. She also said that poverty is the biggest enemy of this region and that Bangladesh wishes to work with everyone to eradicate it. The visiting congress members said, "US has been assisting Bangladesh in its socio-economic development and to ensure food security." They also promised their full cooperation in convincing the US government to increase investments in Bangladesh's power and energy sector. Prime minister's principal secretary MA Karim and ambassador-at-large M Ziauddin were present at the meeting. b
